#import "../../lib.typ": chapter

#chapter(15, "Kazugai Uta's figure faded into the dusk, along with her faint voice.")[
  _"Haizz... What a tiring day..."_

  Kazugai Uta's home resided in a pretty remote suburb area outside of Tokyo,
  which took her about a 30 minute trip to get home from school. Hence, ever
  since middle school, she had been leaving the train much later from her
  friends.

  Today had been quite a long day for her. She was approached by all sorts of
  people because of Mona, to the point she was still talking to some of them
  at this exact moment. While there were some guys who just wanted to ask things
  about Narumi Mona and her sister, she had a couple of interactions that soon
  diverged from the original topic, which gave her some new friends.

  "So yeah, I was talking about that Alice show, y'know, I'm so hyped up for
  that!"

  "The original story is pretty good, yeah. I wonder how good the adaptation
  would go. It'd be funny if it turned out to be the new _Powerpoint Hit_..."

  "Please don't! That's like a generational fumble, can't believe what the
  production committee was thinking... Ah, y'know about _Tea Party at the End of
  the World_?"

  "Hmm? It got some staff announcement, right?"

  "Uhm, I thought there was nothing, but is this Narumi Sena-san's dad?"

  Then, an screenshot of the _Tea Party at the End of the World_ staff
  annoucement post was sent to Uta. There was a big red circle, hastily drawn by
  the one she was messaging with, on the name Narumi Yusuke.

  "No way, is this real?"

  Uta went back to the original post to check, and the name was definitely
  there. There's a obscure rumor that Narumi Sena's dad was a relatively unknown
  music composer, but his name was not explicitly revealed anywhere. Might this
  be yet another coincidence?

  "I'm intrigued. Ah, I'm gonna ask Mona about it."

  "Right! He's Narumi-san's dad too. Share the results to me please!"

  "Okay!"

  _"If this is true, then her family is really stacked..."_

  "Mona! Is this really your dad?"

  Uta then forwarded the image she just got sent. Briefly after, her message was
  seen.

  _"She saw it..."_

  Right then, a message was announced on the train.

  "We are arriving at Naka-meguro Station. Thank you for using Inochi Railway
  today..."

  It was the ever-familiar train annoucement voice, with a bit of static noise.

  With this, Uta's train ride finally got to an end. Putting her phone into the
  bag, she was ready to get out of the train to go back home. She sent a quick
  good-bye to the girl she was talking earlier, before hopping off.

  Stepping out of the door, she was met with the fresh air and the sunset of her
  home city. It was a scene that could awaken a special feeling in anyone.

  Meguro City, the place where Uta lived at, was a suburb region pretty close to
  Tokyo.

  Compared to the populous and bustling Tokyo, Meguro was a much quieter and
  comforting place. Though, it was still a city, so it was much more crowded
  with people than the countryside regions.

  A major downside of living this far to Tokyo was that Uta had to board two
  30-minute train rides every day to school, which was not the end of the world
  but rather a hassle. It was the same situation for her family members too, but
  recently, her parents had their work relocated to her hometown. They wanted to
  get a house in the middle of Tokyo for their children, but it was nothing
  but a fever dream, considering the never-ending rise of house prices.

  Uta began to walk on the same road back home from the station. The crowd
  surrounding her soon dissipated, which seemed to trigger a switch in Uta's
  mind.

  "Chat, it's been a tiring day today."

  "Poor our little streamer... Anyways, how much would you bet that it's Mona's
  dad?"

  "After that Narumi Mona incident, I'd not be surprised if it's actually him."

  "But Rika-chan really has an insane eye. Meanwhile our streamer, I still
  remember her insane throw in that History question."

  "Stop! do not mention it here, I beg of you."

  "'Who is the Prime Minister of Japan following World War 2?' Imagine living in
  Meguro and not getting such a simple question right."

  "I told you, I mistook it with the interim guy! Ahhh-, if I got that one
  right, my grade would be much better..."

  "This is why you never stay up late to study for exams, kids..."

  "Shut up, chat!"

  Kumagai Uta had a deep secret.

  She like to roleplay as an IRL streamer AND her chat at the same time.

  It’s like the eight-grader syndrome in light novels, but it seemed to begin
  much before she entered eighth grade. Sometimes, she could not control this
  side of her, and ended up mumbled something to her friends. Fortunately, the
  most notable response she got was a “You said something?”, so it seemed like
  no one had actually found out about this little secret of her. But if it were
  to be let out somehow, it would be embarrassing to death.

  She suddenly sensed a vibration from her phone in the bag, which she quickly
  reached in to check if something happened. It was Mona, who answered her
  question from earlier.

  "Let's see... 'Uhm- that's right.' Chat, it's actually real..."

  "No way it's actually canon. So Mona's family truly is huge. Unlike some
  particular streamer..."

  "Was there some rumors about her mom being Narumi Ayako too? That extremely
  popular fashion designer? Meanwhile, our Uta is..."

  "Can we stop..."

  "All she talks about recently was Alice brainrot and her legendary fumbles
  during the entrance exams."

  "But chat, you don't know. Alice is peak. Alice is my reason to live. Alice is
  cinema. Absolute peak, masterful writing. And of course the chat could not
  comprehend any of it, this chat is so ass man..."

  "There she goes."

  "More Alice brainrot incoming."

  Uta, for some reason, really liked the _-273.15#[#math.degree]C_ anime, which
  she referred to in short as Alice, named after the titular character.
  According to her, it was a masterpiece in recreating a dystopian atmosphere
  with its theme of nuclear winter and stuff. She tended to yap nonstop about
  the show to the imaginary chat, after already chatted a bunch to real people,
  such as her new friend from earlier.

  "Chat, you have no sense of art at all. You need to know, that Alice, really
  was the pinnacle of storywriting. So many layers of interpretation, which not
  only applies to working people such as the author, but also a mere student
  like me. Ah right! It might applies to you bunch of jobless nitwits, too! But
  you would never get it, I'm afraid..."

  "Hey, censor that word! Chat, our streamer use the j-word again! Please,
  moderators, ban her for the next 14 days, please!"

  "See, all you talk about was stolen jokes from PikPok! So unoriginal..."

  Uta and "her chat" would continue to happily bicker with each other on her
  road home. She said everything out loud, including the chat's supposed
  messages as well as her lines. If an outside observer was watching this, it
  would be something akind to monodrama, which would make them pretty weird out,
  yeah.

  "Uta-nyan, do you have something on your mind?"

  "Not really... I am just tired."

  "Well, being noble to others truly is hard, right?"

  "It's been only two days, and Uta-nyan feels like she does not have any energy
  left..."

  "Chat, I don't want to admit, but maybe I'm not cut out for this..."

  "Of course, right! Uta is not a good person, so just doing something good for
  the sake of others wear her out."

  "Repenting for ones' sins is hard! Especially if you're a horrible person like
  Uta-nyan..."

  "Anyway, you need to lock in right now! If you want to pay all that debt, you
  must act now!"

  "Right! Chat, please stop doomposting and just let me focus on the work. I
  knew that all of my evil deeds would never be amended by my actions, but
  that's the more reason to help others."

  "Will a horrible person like Uta-nyan be able to do it, though?"

  "Or will she just mess up everything?"

  Such questions faded into the dusk, never to be answered.
]
